headline: Shareholders to Demand Action from Mark Zuckerberg and Meta on Child Safety
summary: MENLO PARK, Calif., May 27, 2025--Tomorrow, Meta shareholders will vote on a resolution asking Meta to assess its child safety impacts and whether harm to children on its platform has been reduced. The vote follows reports that the company’s Instagram Teens feature "fails spectacularly on some key dimensions", including promoting sexual, racist, drug and alcohol-related content.
